thoughts: It's tough, because everyone reacts to each situation differently.
This was an interesting survey.  The given scenarios were accessible and easy to evaluate/respond to.

I noticed that all of the subjects of the sentences were female, and I wondered why that was the case. Also, I noticed that two of the sentences outright said that the subjects felt neutral, so I wondered whether those were included just to see if people are paying attention.
I liked this survey a lot, very engaging.
the neutral questions were there to test if i was human i suspect
I liked this study. Thank you.

Maybe if someone wants to write a different feeling in, it should be okay for them to not have to choose one of the pre-determined ones. They should just be able to write it in or click an option N/A and then write the one they think is best.
I clicked the wrong choice on #5
Great survey and I hope my input helps with your research. I enjoyed doing these very much.
question six may have had a misspelling

You have way too many options listed to be 100% sure that participants are actually going through all of them. Also, I can't imagine any sort of meaningful regression analysis could be done with this sort of data.
